      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Realist perspectives prioritize strategic outcomes like regime change and preventing mass violence, suggesting its removal of Gaddafi was a significant victory. A more objective assessment requires distinguishing between tactical and strategic success. While the military objective (regime removal) was achieved, the strategic goal of fostering a stable post-intervention state proved elusive, leading to lasting geopolitical complications.",
      "source": "target",
